        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4914661" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer455821901121951532">Alys is an independent girl running her father&apos;s shop during his illness, when she is accused of being a witch by her neighbors, who really just want her shop. She is tied up outside the village and left for the dragon that has been rampaging to eat.<br/>But when he arrives, instead of eating Alys, he offers her a chance to take revenge on her enemies. Should Alys take the dragon up on his offer? Wouldn&apos;t it be ironic if she ended up committing the crimes she has already been found guilty of doing?<br/>Cl</span>
  <span id="freeText455821901121951532" style="display:none">Alys is an independent girl running her father's shop during his illness, when she is accused of being a witch by her neighbors, who really just want her shop. She is tied up outside the village and left for the dragon that has been rampaging to eat.<br />But when he arrives, instead of eating Alys, he offers her a chance to take revenge on her enemies. Should Alys take the dragon up on his offer? Wouldn't it be ironic if she ended up committing the crimes she has already been found guilty of doing?<br />Clever, funny, and with a surprise twist at the end, I found this to be a very satisfying read. </span>
