              <span id="reviewTextContainer88918163" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13923567595248357662">Not your usual fantasy tropes - what happens when the girl staked out for the dragon to eat, insteads joins forces with him to get revenge on her tormentors?<br/>This quite good (albeit short) book.<br/>I really enjoyed how the author did not &apos;humanize&apos; the dragon, but instead constantly reminded the reader how alien he was, how he did not think like a human. <br/>I definitely read more adventures of Alys and Selandrine.</span>
  <span id="freeText13923567595248357662" style="display:none">Not your usual fantasy tropes - what happens when the girl staked out for the dragon to eat, insteads joins forces with him to get revenge on her tormentors?<br />This quite good (albeit short) book.<br />I really enjoyed how the author did not 'humanize' the dragon, but instead constantly reminded the reader how alien he was, how he did not think like a human. <br />I definitely read more adventures of Alys and Selandrine.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13923567595248357662" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


