        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer937886878" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3872493192529952855">It took me a day and a half to finish this book. It was short, i think it was the shortest fantasy book I&apos;ve ever read.<br/><br/>It&apos;s a standalone and as such it is entertaining as a light read, it lacks depth. <br/>This is what I think happened: this book came out in the period where fantasy was more marginalized than SF (can you tell I&apos;m not a SF lover at all?) and during this time it was thought that children and teens have the attention span of mice so fantasy novels that exceeded 450 pages were considered</span>
  <span id="freeText3872493192529952855" style="display:none">It took me a day and a half to finish this book. It was short, i think it was the shortest fantasy book I've ever read.<br /><br />It's a standalone and as such it is entertaining as a light read, it lacks depth. <br />This is what I think happened: this book came out in the period where fantasy was more marginalized than SF (can you tell I'm not a SF lover at all?) and during this time it was thought that children and teens have the attention span of mice so fantasy novels that exceeded 450 pages were considered already too long, so they cut them into sections of 300-400 pages per volume. though to be fair I dunno how Wheel of Time and Sword of Truth got past the cut *shrug*. <br /><br />This novella stems from that time period and it would have been interesting as a standalone novel of 600 pages set in fantasy - young adult genre. It had promise. I don't know why the author did not broaden it. <br /><br />The plot is fairly plain and unambitious, fast paced (because it's a barely 200 page book) and lacks character development, world-building and atmosphere. Three things that make a fantasy a fantasy. It's good as a light read.<br />(Sidenote: The Dragon transforming into a 17 year old boy, made me think of the Dragon Aspects from World of Warcraft, there's that)<br /><br />So I guess that was a short review. Then again it is a short novel. <br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/29879367-madalina-mocanu?order=d&amp;sort=review&amp;view=reviews#" rel="nofollow noopener">My other reviews :D</a><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3872493192529952855" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
