<span id="freeTextContainer2501216256184721860">This is one of the best books that I have read in a long time. Alys is accused of witchcraft and therefor left, tied up, on a mountain by the people of her village, to be eaten by the small dragon roaming nearby. She gets free before she sees the dragon and wonders what to do. Then she see&apos;s the dragon. She kind of wants to get this over with so she starts throwing rocks at it to get it&apos;s attention. The dragon soars over andturns into a 17-year-old man, Selendrile. Instead of eating her, he offe</span>
  <span id="freeText2501216256184721860" style="display:none">This is one of the best books that I have read in a long time. Alys is accused of witchcraft and therefor left, tied up, on a mountain by the people of her village, to be eaten by the small dragon roaming nearby. She gets free before she sees the dragon and wonders what to do. Then she see's the dragon. She kind of wants to get this over with so she starts throwing rocks at it to get it's attention. The dragon soars over andturns into a 17-year-old man, Selendrile. Instead of eating her, he offers his help for her to get revenge on the people who made the accusations. She agrees and they set out to get revenge.<br /><br />I loved the entire book from start to finish and am happy to give it 5 stars! </span>
