<div id="review_2907197923" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2907197923" />
    <a title="Erin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44277021-erin"><img alt="Erin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552179771p2/44277021.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2907197923?book_show_action=true">Jul 22, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erin" href="/user/show/44277021-erin">Erin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44277021-erin?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44277021-erin?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44277021-erin?shelf=book-brigade">book-brigade</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2907197923" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12629559170916236984">I&apos;m trying to take into consideration that this is a children&apos;s book as I write my review. The book was an incredibly fast read. I finished it in one sitting. <br/><br/>As for the story, I think what stuck out to me the most while reading is how incredibly bare bones it was. We know nothing that is not incredibly vital information -there&apos;s not really any world building and both the setting and list of characters are so tight that the world, despite having magic and dragons, feels very closed and small. Ad</span>
  <span id="freeText12629559170916236984" style="display:none">I'm trying to take into consideration that this is a children's book as I write my review. The book was an incredibly fast read. I finished it in one sitting. <br /><br />As for the story, I think what stuck out to me the most while reading is how incredibly bare bones it was. We know nothing that is not incredibly vital information -there's not really any world building and both the setting and list of characters are so tight that the world, despite having magic and dragons, feels very closed and small. Additionally, the dragon's motivation for helping Alys is never revealed or explained beyond "he felt like it." Seems kinda lame, especially when *SPOILER ALERT* he ends up murdering on her behalf.<br /><br />Also because it's a children's book, I thought it was odd how much seeing each other naked, virginity, and sex were brought up between Alys and the dragon dude. Is that normal? </span>
  <a data-text-id="12629559170916236984" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


